pix_threshold_depth
======================================

pure data / Gem external to filter out certain parts in a defined x,y,z region of the depthmap provided by Kinect camera via pix_freenect or pix_openni.


(C) 2012 by Matthias Kronlachner
__________________________________________________________

pix_openni and pix_freenect can (if set to raw mm mode) output the depth information in millimeter in the red and green color channel.

this external allows you to filter out parts of the depthmap that lie within a certain x,y,z range.
you can easily create masks for tracking or projection. (in combination with pix_multiblob...)

all computation is done on cpu!
consider using gpu shaders if you don't need the data on cpu side!

